# Architect OS — Execution Layer
## Functional Spec: Execution Overview Page

**Document Type:** Functional Specification — Pre-Build
**Follows:** `ArchitectOS_Execution_Layer_FunctionalSpec.md`
**Purpose:** Define the complete feature set, layout, states, interactions, and data requirements for the Execution Overview page — the navigation hub for the entire execution layer.

---

## Page Purpose

The Execution Overview is the first page a founder sees when they enter the Execution section. Its job is to orient, inform, and direct — telling the founder exactly where they are in their sprint lifecycle and what the most important next action is. It is not a dashboard. It is not a reporting surface. It is a smart doorway that changes based on context.

The page has one primary question it must answer at every visit: *"What does this founder need to do or know right now?"* The layout, the content, and the navigation cards on this page all answer that question differently depending on sprint state.

---

## Sprint Naming Convention

### Default System Name
When a sprint is created, the platform assigns a default name using the following format:

**"Sprint [N] — [Truncated Goal]"**

- N = sequential sprint number for this account (1, 2, 3...)
- Truncated goal = the first 6–8 words of the sprint goal, followed by an ellipsis if needed
- Example: *"Sprint 1 — Stabilize delivery floor and reduce founder..."*

### Founder Override
The sprint name is always editable. An edit icon appears inline next to the sprint name wherever it is displayed on this page. Clicking it activates an inline text input. The founder can name their sprint anything they want:
- "Q1 2026"
- "The Stabilization Quarter"
- "Foundation Sprint"
- "Jan–Apr 2026"

The custom name replaces the system default everywhere the sprint name appears — across the execution section, sprint history, and any exported documents.

**Behavior rules:**
- Name input: single-line text, max 60 characters
- Save on blur — auto-save pattern consistent with the rest of the platform
- If left blank and blurred: reverts to system default name
- The sprint goal is always shown as a subtitle regardless of what the sprint name is set to — so even if the founder names it something abstract, the goal text remains visible for context

