## Sprint Lifecycle States

The Execution Overview page renders differently across six distinct sprint states. Every layout decision below is state-aware.

| State | Trigger | Primary Founder Action |
|---|---|---|
| **No Sprint** | No sprint has been locked yet | Begin planning |
| **Pre-Launch** | Sprint locked, kickoff date not set or in future | Set kickoff date, share launch summary |
| **Active** | Kickoff date has passed, < 63 days elapsed | Update progress, run standups |
| **Wind-Down** | 63–84 days elapsed (final 21 days) | Complete wind-down review |
| **Closed — Retro Pending** | 84 days elapsed or manually closed, retrospective not started | Begin retrospective |
| **Closed — Complete** | Retrospective approved and finalized | Begin next sprint planning |

All state transitions are automatic based on the kickoff date and 84-day sprint duration — except the Closed state, which can also be triggered manually by the founder via a "Close Sprint Early" option in the page settings menu.

