## State 2 — Pre-Launch

### When It Renders
The sprint is locked. The executive summary has been generated. The kickoff date has either not been set yet, or has been set to a future date. The sprint clock has not started.

### What the Founder Needs
Two things: set the kickoff date, and share the launch summary with the team. These are the only actions that matter in this state. Everything else waits.

### Layout

**Sprint Identity Block** — as defined above. Status badge shows PRE-LAUNCH. Dates show: "Kicks off [date]" if set, or "Kickoff date not set" in amber if not yet set.

**Primary Action Banner**
A visually distinct banner below the sprint identity block — not a card, a full-width prompt:

If kickoff date is NOT set:
- Amber left border treatment
- Heading: *"Set your sprint kickoff date to start the clock."*
- Body: *"Your sprint plan is locked and ready. Choose the date your team officially kicks off this sprint — this is when your 84-day countdown begins."*
- Inline date picker — founder selects the kickoff date directly in this banner
- "Confirm Kickoff Date" button — saves the date and transitions the banner to the confirmation state

If kickoff date IS set (and is in the future):
- Blue/neutral left border
- Heading: *"Sprint [name] kicks off on [date]."*
- Body: *"Share your sprint launch summary with your team before the kickoff meeting."*
- Two action buttons: "View Launch Summary" and "Share with Team"
- Edit link: "Change kickoff date"

**Navigation Cards — Pre-Launch State**
Four cards shown below the primary action banner. Sprint Launch is fully active. The others are visible but in a pre-active state — they show their title and description but their status lines reflect that the sprint hasn't started yet.

| Card | State | Status Line |
|---|---|---|
| Sprint Launch | **Active** — primary card | "Review and share your launch summary" |
| Status Tracker | Muted — not yet active | "Available once your sprint begins" |
| Momentum Synthesis | Muted — not yet active | "Available once your sprint begins" |
| Retrospective | Muted — not yet active | "Available at sprint close" |

Muted cards are visible but not clickable. They use a reduced opacity treatment and a lock icon in the corner. This is aspirational — it shows the founder what's coming without making the state feel broken.

