## State 3 — Active Sprint (Primary Design Target)

### When It Renders
The kickoff date has passed and fewer than 63 days have elapsed. The sprint is in full motion.

### Layout

**Sprint Identity Block** — status badge: ACTIVE. Days remaining pill visible.

**Sprint Health Bar**
A horizontal summary strip directly below the sprint identity block. Four metrics displayed side by side:

| Metric | Content | Visual |
|---|---|---|
| Overall Completion | Percentage of milestones marked Complete | Progress bar + percentage |
| Initiatives | "X of Y complete" | Simple count |
| Blockers | "N blocked" | Amber text + dot if > 0; muted if 0 |
| Last Updated | "Updated [N days ago]" | Muted if ≤ 3 days; amber if 4–7 days; soft warning if > 7 days |

The health bar is read-only — no interactions. It is a quick-glance surface only. Clicking anywhere on it navigates to the Status Tracker.

**Navigation Cards — Active State**
Four cards, all fully active. Arranged in a 2×2 grid on desktop, single column stack on mobile.

---

**Card 1 — Sprint Launch**
- Icon: rocket or flag
- Title: "Sprint Launch"
- Description: "Your sprint summary and team alignment document."
- Status line: "Shared with team · Locked [date]" if shared. "Not yet shared" in amber if not shared.
- Action needed state: if the launch summary has not been shared, a subtle "Share with team" badge appears on the card
- Click: navigates to Sprint Launch page

---

**Card 2 — Status Tracker**
- Icon: checklist or progress circle
- Title: "Status Tracker"
- Description: "Update milestone progress and run your weekly standup."
- Status line: dynamic — shows the most relevant current data point:
  - If updated in last 3 days: "Last updated [N days ago] · [X] milestones complete"
  - If not updated in 4–7 days: "Last updated [N days ago]" in amber
  - If not updated in 8+ days: "No updates in [N] days — consider a check-in" in amber
- Secondary stat: "[N] milestones targeted this month" — pulls from milestones where timeline = current month
- Click: navigates to Status Tracker

---

**Card 3 — Momentum Synthesis**
- Icon: compass or waveform
- Title: "Momentum Synthesis"
- Description: "Get a strategic read on how your quarter is progressing."
- Status line:
  - If never generated: "Generate your first synthesis" — with a subtle prompt treatment
  - If generated: "Last generated [date] · Week [N] of 12"
- A note below the status line if synthesis is more than 2 weeks old: "Your synthesis may not reflect recent progress."
- Click: navigates to Momentum Synthesis page

---

**Card 4 — Retrospective** *(muted in active state)*
- Icon: reflection/mirror
- Title: "Retrospective"
- Description: "Close the quarter with a full synthesis of what you built."
- Status line: "Available at sprint close · [N] days remaining"
- State: visible but not clickable — muted opacity, lock icon
- This card exists in the active state so the founder always knows it's coming. It is not hidden.

---

**Wind-Down Prompt — Active State (Day 56+)**
Starting at day 56 (4 weeks from end), a subtle informational strip appears between the health bar and the navigation cards — not alarming, just orienting:

*"You have [N] days remaining in Sprint [name]. Wind-down review becomes available in [X] days."*

This transitions to the full wind-down banner when the state changes.

