## State 4 — Wind-Down

### When It Renders
63 to 84 days have elapsed since kickoff. Final 21 days of the sprint.

### Layout

**Sprint Identity Block** — status badge: WIND-DOWN. Days remaining pill shown in amber.

**Wind-Down Banner**
A full-width banner, more prominent than the active state's informational strip:
- Amber left border
- Heading: *"Sprint [name] ends in [N] days."*
- Body: *"Begin your wind-down review to close this quarter with intention — decide what to complete, what to carry forward, and what to release."*
- CTA button: "Begin Wind-Down Review" — links to the Sprint Wind-Down page
- If wind-down is in progress: button changes to "Continue Wind-Down Review" with a progress indicator showing which of the three steps are complete

**Sprint Health Bar** — same as active state.

**Navigation Cards — Wind-Down State**
Five cards now visible — the Wind-Down card activates and moves to the top of the card grid.

| Card | Position | State |
|---|---|---|
| Sprint Wind-Down | **First — most prominent** | Active, highlighted with subtle amber border |
| Status Tracker | Second | Active |
| Momentum Synthesis | Third | Active |
| Sprint Launch | Fourth | Active — reduced emphasis |
| Retrospective | Fifth | Muted — "Available at sprint close" |

**Wind-Down Card (new):**
- Icon: hourglass or sunset
- Title: "Sprint Wind-Down"
- Description: "Close this quarter with intention — complete, carry forward, or release."
- Status line: shows wind-down progress — "Step 1 of 3 complete" or "Not started"
- Action needed state: if not started, a "Begin" badge appears
- Click: navigates to Sprint Wind-Down page

