## State 5 — Closed, Retrospective Pending

### When It Renders
84 days have elapsed from the kickoff date, or the founder has manually closed the sprint. The retrospective has not yet been started.

### Layout

**Sprint Identity Block** — status badge: CLOSED. No days remaining pill.

**Retrospective CTA Banner**
Full-width, prominent — this is the primary action in this state:
- Blue/celebration left border treatment
- Heading: *"Sprint [name] is complete."*
- Body: *"Take a moment to close this chapter. Your retrospective synthesizes what you accomplished, how your capabilities developed, and what comes next."*
- CTA button: "Begin Retrospective" — links to Retrospective page

**Sprint Completion Summary**
A simple summary block below the banner:
- Milestones completed: [N] of [N]
- Initiatives completed: [N] of [N]
- Days in sprint: [N]
- Sprint goal self-assessment: "Pending — answer in your retrospective"

**Navigation Cards — Closed State**
Cards simplified — only relevant completed sections remain active:

| Card | State | Note |
|---|---|---|
| Retrospective | **Primary — active, highlighted** | The main action |
| Status Tracker | Active — read-only reference | Founders may still want to view |
| Sprint Launch | Active — historical reference | View the launch summary |
| Momentum Synthesis | Active — historical reference | View past syntheses |
| Sprint Wind-Down | Read-only | Decisions are locked |

---

## State 6 — Closed, Retrospective Complete

### When It Renders
The retrospective has been approved and finalized by the founder.

### Layout

**Sprint Identity Block** — status badge: CLOSED + "Retrospective Complete" secondary tag.

**Celebration Block**
A full-width acknowledgment moment — calm and considered, not exuberant:
- Heading: *"[Sprint name] is documented and complete."*
- Sprint Theme — displayed prominently: the one-line theme from the Sprint Launch, now serving as the closing summary of the quarter
- Sprint Theme Close — the AI-generated closing line from the retrospective, shown below the theme

**Sprint Summary Strip**
Three key numbers from the completed sprint:
- Milestones completed: [N]
- Capability areas advanced: [N] (count of areas where score increased)
- Sprint goal outcome: Achieved / Partially Achieved / We Learned

**Forward Action — Primary CTA**
*"Ready to begin [Sprint 2 / next quarter]?"*
Button: "Begin Sprint 2 Planning" — links to the Planning section with the Quarter Map pre-populated from the retrospective's Forward Guidance.

Secondary link: "View Sprint [N] Retrospective" — links to the completed retrospective as a historical record.

**Sprint History Preview**
A collapsed section at the bottom: "Your Sprint History." If this is Sprint 1, it shows just this sprint. As sprints accumulate, this section shows a row per completed sprint with: sprint name, dates, milestone completion rate, and a link to the retrospective. This is the beginning of the longitudinal record.

